{
  "stem": "5810.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At the time it wasn't explained to me exactly what they were doing to Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't think that anyone knew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But we certainly knew that we were different then, and that life was changing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this is when I began to understand things were not the same any longer.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it came quite early.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, again, to go back to the fact that we were wearing the Jewish star, and the fact that many Jews were-- were taken by force, and beaten on the streets because they were Jews, and my questions were, why were they doing that to those people?",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was explained in simple terms, that because they were Jews, I started now fearing the fact that this could happen to me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so as much as I could, I-- I wore the star, but I hid the star as much as I could hide the star.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So fear began to come, as I remember it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I used to be able to walk by German soldiers, all of a sudden, if I could I would have gone across the street rather than pass them near, or being near to them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I no longer spoke to my mother and father in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I started speaking to them in French.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those were the first little signs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The bigger sign, when I knew that things were totally different, is-- and I'm certainly jumping a little bit on that-- but one day I was playing on the street by myself by that time, because no one was playing with me any longer, at least the gentiles weren't.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then the Jews somehow weren't on the streets anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I still insisted on playing on the street right in front of the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
